As part of its plans to encourage domestic Tourism, the Ministry of Information and Culture has planned for Saturday this week, “Nigerian Flavours,” an event put together in a collaboration between NIHOTOUR, NTA and Nigerian Tourism Development Corporation, ( NTDC ).
The event would be holding at Harrow Park, Wuse, Abuja from midday.
Nigerian Flavours showcases the rich culinary diversity in Nigerian cuisine and delicacies. It focuses attention on Nigeria’s rich and diverse culinary heritage and tradition.
This landmark event would hold in the City of Abuja, a safe family oriented, clean, peaceful and fast growing tourism destination.
